rPJ_A\/XZaouZgHi7I\/AAAAAAAAhNA\/NiZzqKIRNqIQXaKfG39CWG6yNDduNd9CwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wR_EUcKjk2GY_X-g.png","title":"Sweet Potato Crust Pizza","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pizza Bases"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"350 g dried chickpeas"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 - 3 sweet potatoes (approx. 300-350 g), peeled, diced (2-3 cm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp bicarbonate of soda"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ - 1 tsp dried mixed herbs, to taste"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Tomato Sauce"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 garlic clove"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g onions, quartered"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"20 g olive oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"400 g tinned chopped tomatoes"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g tomato purée"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp dried oregano"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"&frac18; tsp ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g Cheddar cheese, grated"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"60 g pepperoni, or topping of choice"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1825 kJ \/ 437 kcal","18.5 g","34.2 g","23 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["An alternative gluten-free pizza base that's easy with Thermomix. In this nutritious option you make your own chickpea flour before mixing it with steamed sweet potatoes to create a simple yet tasty allergy-friendly pizza base. Just bake the bases, add your favourite toppings and grill for a few minutes – it’s that simple!","If the mixture looks too dry to form a rollable dough, add a little water after mashing in <b>step 4.<b>","Simmer the tomato sauce for longer for a thicker consistency.","For a smoother tomato sauce, after simmering in <b>step 7<b>, blend <b>1 min\/speed 5-7,<b> increasing speed gradually<b>."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}